						<div class="postbody">I like working with 8 bit speed variable, the high 4 bits being the pixel increment per frame and the 4 low bits represents the 1/16 internal counter increment.
<br />You'd never want to move a sprite slower than 1/16 pixel a frame, and never faster than 8+7/16 pixels a frame, so this enable you to work with easy 8-bit speeds, $10 being the standard 1 pixel per frame speed.</div>

					
