						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You'd never want to move a sprite slower than 1/16 pixel a frame</div>
<br />But you may want to <em>accelerate</em> a sprite slower than 1/16 pixel per frame per frame. For instance, at 16 pixels = 1 meter and 60.0988 frames = 1 second, standard Earth gravity is 0.0434 pixels per frame per frame, or 0.695 of your units.</div>

