<br />Tokumaru : You're speaking of signed speed variables. In my game engine I'm writing for my action-adventure game, I only have speed on projectiles, but monsters are animated by their own AI so they can move at constant or variable speed if they have a programm to move them their way, and the player always move at the constant speed of 1.5 pixels per frame (assuming it moves). I don't use signed variables for speed, but rather another direction variable. So it is easier for a monster to create a new projectile with the same speed, but another direction. The direction byte also serves to determine wich sprite is shown on player/monster (and possibly projectiles too if they're not bland round). I didn't say it is the best way, but it is like I did, and my game engine isn't finished yet.</div>

					
